<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 4:14AM EDT  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...Heavy Rain Likely Before Daybreak...
A large area of heavy showers and thunderstorms over the Niagara
Peninsula and eastern Lake Erie at 4:15 AM EDT will move across
Grand Island and parts of Niagara county between 4:30 and 5:30 AM.
This general area has already picked up a general inch to an inch
and a half of rain since late last evening...and additional
rainfall before daybreak could match that. The greatest chance
for significant heavy rain from tropical downpours will be over
the western half of Niagara county.
The area of showers and thunderstorms will be accompanied by a
fair amount of lightning.</description>
